How to use it

  Three agents, used in order through your AI coding assistant:

  1. Planner — describe what you want, it asks questions and outputs an
     architecture spec.
  2. Builder — takes the spec, writes the system prompt.
  3. Reviewer — tests and evaluates the prompt. Approves or sends it back.

  Commands:

     Claude Code    /prompt-architect-planner
                    /prompt-architect-builder
                    /prompt-architect-reviewer

     OpenCode       @prompt-architect-planner
                    @prompt-architect-builder
                    @prompt-architect-reviewer

  Flow: Planner -> Builder -> Reviewer -> (approve or iterate)

  Quick edits: skip the Planner, go straight to Builder then Reviewer.

  Full pipeline guide: prompts/templates/meta-task-create-agent.md


